generic/319
generic/444

# --- Large-file block accounting across remount ---
#   generic/694 verifies that stat(2) i_blocks stays stable for a file larger
#   than 4 GiB after _test_cycle_mount. Keep excluded until large-file block
#   accounting and remount persistence are validated end-to-end on TideFS FUSE.
#   Focused mounted validation and any required accounting fix are tracked by
#   #2229; this exclusion stays until that row passes.
generic/694

# --- Linux fscrypt policy/key ioctls (unsupported/refused) ---
#   generic/397-401 exercise Linux fscrypt policy/key behavior. The TideFS
#   FUSE preview does not implement fscrypt compatibility; its ioctl boundary
#   wires only FS_IOC_FIEMAP, FS_IOC_FSGETXATTR, and TIDEFS_IOC_DEFRAG, with
#   other commands refused as EOPNOTSUPP by FuseVfsAdapter::ioctl in
#   apps/tidefs-posix-filesystem-adapter-daemon/src/fuse_vfs_adapter.rs. This
#   is separate from mounted device-transform encryption, which remains
#   blocked by transform authority.
generic/397
generic/398
generic/399
generic/400
generic/401

# --- Immutable/append-only flags ---
#   FS_IMMUTABLE_FL/FS_APPEND_FL enforcement is now wired into the FUSE adapter
#   (write/truncate/chmod/chown/unlink/rmdir/rename/symlink/mkdir/link/fallocate).
#   generic/079 exercises immutable/append-only behavior and should pass.


# --- Row-classified FUSE ioctl/kernel-specific exclusions (#1934) ---
#   generic/009 exercises FALLOC_FL_ZERO_RANGE through xfs_io fzero plus
#   FIEMAP extent checks. TideFS wires zero-range fallocate, but the mounted
#   row remains excluded until zero-range plus FIEMAP is validated end-to-end.
generic/009

#   generic/048 needs scratch shutdown, sync/shutdown/remount recovery, and
#   FIEMAP/extent checks. The FUSE preview has no mounted filesystem shutdown
#   or log-replay boundary.
generic/048

#   generic/054 is another shutdown/log-replay row with version-2 log
#   configuration coverage; it stays in the shutdown/recovery operator gap.
generic/054

#   generic/058 exercises standard FALLOC_FL_INSERT_RANGE through xfs_io
#   finsert plus FIEMAP extent checks. TideFS source has insert-range handling,
#   but this row shares the insert-range/FIEMAP validation boundary tracked by
#   #1926 before the exclusion can be removed.
generic/058

#   generic/062 is a broad xattr namespace row across user/trusted/security
#   attrs, special nodes, symlinks, and backup/restore traversal. It is an
#   xattr namespace/special-node validation gap rather than a generic ioctl row.
generic/062

