# --- Linux quota API/tooling (not TideFS internal quota admission) ---
#   generic/244 exercises quotactl Q_GETNEXTQUOTA plus user/group quota tools.
#   generic/383 exercises xfs_quota project-quota setup/reporting. TideFS
#   internal quota/reserve accounting is separate from Linux quota UAPI/tool
#   compatibility, so these rows remain excluded until that mounted UAPI is
#   deliberately implemented or refused.
generic/244
generic/383

# --- Directory rename errno evidence pending ---
#   generic/245 is not a quota row: it verifies rename over a non-empty
#   directory returns EEXIST or ENOTEMPTY. The FUSE rename mapper currently
#   maps NamespaceError::AlreadyExists to EEXIST and NamespaceError::NotEmpty
#   to ENOTEMPTY in fuse_rename.rs, but the mounted row remains excluded until
#   it is verified end-to-end.
generic/245

# --- Swapfile activation / kernel file mapping ---
#   generic/472 exercises swapon oddities. TideFS FUSE does not currently
#   provide a FUSE_BMAP mapping path for kernel swapfile activation; the
#   FuseVfsAdapter::bmap path returns EOPNOTSUPP through
#   unsupported_vfs_bmap_errno().
generic/472

# --- Active swapfile dedupe/reflink refusal ---
#   generic/493 expects dedupe against an active swapfile to fail with
#   ETXTBSY. Its xfstests prerequisite first requires working swapfile
#   activation, and classify_vfs_ioctl_command() also refuses FIDEDUPERANGE
#   with EOPNOTSUPP. Keep excluded until activation, mounted dedupe, and the
#   active-swapfile refusal are validated together.
generic/493

# --- Active swapfile truncate / hole-punch refusal ---
#   generic/494 expects truncate and hole-punch against an active swapfile to
#   fail with ETXTBSY. Its xfstests prerequisite first requires working
#   swapfile activation, which cannot pass while FuseVfsAdapter::bmap returns
#   EOPNOTSUPP. Keep excluded until activation and both refusal paths are
#   validated together.
generic/494

# --- Freeze/thaw (FIFREEZE/FITHAW unsupported/refused on FUSE) ---
#   generic/068, generic/085, and generic/275 exercise the Linux filesystem
#   freeze/thaw ioctl boundary. TideFS FUSE deliberately refuses FIFREEZE and
#   FITHAW as EOPNOTSUPP in FuseVfsAdapter::ioctl; mounted-kernel freeze/thaw
#   remains a separate issue.
generic/068
generic/085
generic/275

# --- Insert/collapse range row validation (#1926) ---
#   Focused FUSE xfstests run 29188560825 requested generic/060,
#   generic/061, generic/063, generic/064, and generic/072. The rows were not
#   runnable: generic/060-064 stopped at xfs_io fiemap prechecks, and
#   generic/072 stopped at the xfs_io fcollapse precheck.
#   FUSE fallocate dispatch and the local filesystem engine wire
#   FALLOC_FL_INSERT_RANGE and FALLOC_FL_COLLAPSE_RANGE. These rows stay
#   excluded until delayed-allocation/multi-insert, mixed insert/collapse,
#   and collapse/truncate stress behavior is validated end-to-end with FIEMAP
#   and filesystem consistency checks.
generic/060
generic/061
generic/063
generic/064
generic/072

# --- RENAME_WHITEOUT (Linux/overlayfs-specific; rejected fail-closed) ---
